01:41:45.530 --> 01:41:49.090
So it gets you -- you obtain
only the outer surface

01:41:49.090 --> 01:41:51.880
of the object and
not the inside.

01:41:51.880 --> 01:41:57.050
But still, it's an arm that
you can bring to the museum

01:41:57.050 --> 01:42:01.480
and you don't have to move
the instrument to the CT scan.

01:42:01.480 --> 01:42:06.040
So it's very easy and
there's a very good resolution

01:42:06.040 --> 01:42:09.520
and you get directly on the
computer why you acquire --

01:42:09.520 --> 01:42:14.730
you swipe the laser
line on the object

01:42:14.730 --> 01:42:17.360
and you collect a 3D surface.

01:42:17.360 --> 01:42:20.110
Then, like in the
multispectral imaging,

01:42:20.110 --> 01:42:25.070
you can make substraction like
