01:42:58.290 --> 01:43:02.460
But there are movements
of the soundboard.

01:43:02.460 --> 01:43:05.880
And you see this, usually
the soundboard is here,

01:43:05.880 --> 01:43:08.030
touching here, the soundboard.

01:43:08.030 --> 01:43:10.060
But the consequences
and the evolution

01:43:10.060 --> 01:43:12.760
of the hate also
come up to here.

01:43:12.760 --> 01:43:14.840
You see it's bluer here.

01:43:14.840 --> 01:43:18.090
And it means that the
whole structure is moving

01:43:18.090 --> 01:43:19.700
in a complex way.

01:43:19.700 --> 01:43:23.680
So in the idea of the
risk assessment we take

01:43:23.680 --> 01:43:26.090
when we make a modification
of the instrument

01:43:26.090 --> 01:43:28.680
when we setup even a song post,

01:43:28.680 --> 01:43:31.440
this kind of tools
could be very useful.

01:43:31.440 --> 01:43:36.940
On a -- at a larger scale,
when we make this substraction

01:43:36.940 --> 01:43:41.870
after treatment minus
before treatment,

01:43:41.870 --> 01:43:46.190
we see a general
modification of the violins

01:43:46.190 --> 01:43:50.160
where when you string the --
when you tune the instrument

01:43:50.160 --> 01:43:55.230
when it's strung, obviously
the soundboards go lower

01:43:55.230 --> 01:43:57.590
because of the pressure
of the bridge.

01:43:57.590 --> 01:43:59.440
And it's -- what is the scale?

01:43:59.440 --> 01:44:03.540
It's about one millimeter
lower deflection of this area,

01:44:03.540 --> 01:44:06.340
which is not -- it's
a lot when you think

01:44:06.340 --> 01:44:10.750
that the soundboard is two
and a half millimeter thick.

01:44:10.750 --> 01:44:16.250
And interestingly also we see
that come relatively in terms

01:44:16.250 --> 01:44:21.790
of relative position, the scroll
I mean, [inaudible] is going

01:44:21.790 --> 01:44:24.850
up when you pull the strings.

01:44:24.850 --> 01:44:28.680
And this kind of
modifications help also

01:44:28.680 --> 01:44:31.140
and it gives you a
range of the scale

01:44:31.140 --> 01:44:33.800
and the magnitude
of these changes.

01:44:33.800 --> 01:44:36.790
And it's like the movement --

01:44:36.790 --> 01:44:40.540
or relative movement of the
scroll is one millimeter also,

01:44:40.540 --> 01:44:43.940
approximately in
the other direction.

01:44:43.940 --> 01:44:46.560
So the soundboard is
going one millimeter down,

01:44:46.560 --> 01:44:50.910
roughly speaking, and the scroll
is going one millimeter up.

01:44:50.910 --> 01:44:55.760
So if you want to treat and we
are planning to use this kind

01:44:55.760 --> 01:45:02.980
of 3D methodological tools to
follow, to monitor instrument

01:45:02.980 --> 01:45:04.840
that are kept in condition.

01:45:04.840 --> 01:45:11.450
It might be a way to follow
and to detect early enough

01:45:11.450 --> 01:45:13.410
if the structure
