02:06:33.590 --> 02:06:34.890
&gt;&gt; Lynn Brostoff: Yeah.

02:06:34.890 --> 02:06:38.120
I think the literature
is a little bit confusing

02:06:38.120 --> 02:06:41.950
about fluorescence of glass
and a lot of people felt

02:06:41.950 --> 02:06:44.570
that it was just unpredictable.

02:06:44.570 --> 02:06:49.000
But we are fortunate that
[inaudible] always put

02:06:49.000 --> 02:06:53.140
that little dash
of manganese in.

02:06:53.140 --> 02:06:57.090
And because of that
manganese we can tell

02:06:57.090 --> 02:06:59.970
that it does have a
characteristic fluorescence

02:06:59.970 --> 02:07:04.470
which was that yellowy green
color that Stephanie showed.

02:07:04.470 --> 02:07:08.910
And in fact, it's very
important in UV examination

02:07:08.910 --> 02:07:13.230
to use two wavelengths so you
can use long and short UV.

02:07:13.230 --> 02:07:16.740
And the fluorescence is
a little bit different.

02:07:16.740 --> 02:07:20.220
And we are now batting 100%

02:07:20.220 --> 02:07:23.660
in predicting whether we
have a high leaded glass

02:07:23.660 --> 02:07:27.540
or a potash glass for
[inaudible] flutes

02:07:27.540 --> 02:07:30.150
because remember,
they're a formulation.

02:07:30.150 --> 02:07:33.420
So that's not just
potassium and silicon,

02:07:33.420 --> 02:07:34.720
there's a lot of other things.

02:07:34.720 --> 02:07:37.060
Or it's not just
lead in silicon.

02:07:37.060 --> 02:07:41.540
And yes, it's very
characteristically

02:07:41.540 --> 02:07:43.800
that yellowy green color.

02:07:43.800 --> 02:07:47.040
And the leaded ones are
also known in shortwave

02:07:47.040 --> 02:07:49.890
to be what people call icy blue.

02:07:49.890 --> 02:07:53.450
And the combination of
that pink and the icy blue

02:07:53.450 --> 02:07:55.810
and the two wavelengths
is very definitive

02:07:55.810 --> 02:07:58.710
for those highlighted glasses.

02:07:58.710 --> 02:08:01.130
So as I said, we've been
using this technique

02:08:01.130 --> 02:08:05.470
and we're literally 100%
spot on in predicting

02:08:05.470 --> 02:08:07.970
which type of glass it is.

